{# Agent task: materialize the approved design to disk. #}
# Materialize the skill

Approved design: `{{ upstream['design-review'].task_path }}`.
Gather output: `{{ upstream['gather'].task_path }}` (provides
`name` and `location`).

## Task

For each entry in `design.files`, `fs_write` the file at
`~/.kiro/skills/<location>/<name>/<file.path>`. Generate
content per `content_outline`, applying the type-specific
conventions you read during design.

For SKILL.md, generate frontmatter + sections per
`design.frontmatter` and `design.sections`. Section bodies
follow the type-specific convention file (workflow type uses
the unified template — see below).

## Output

Construct `output.yaml` (matching `schemas/files.yaml`) via
loom's schema-driven writer. `fs_write` is for the skill
files; the task output goes through `loom output`.

```bash
LOOM=~/.kiro/skills/home/loom/scripts/loom.sh
WD={{ run.workdir }}

$LOOM output init "$WD" --task skill-materialize

$LOOM output add "$WD" --task skill-materialize \
    --set 'files[].path=/abs/path/to/SKILL.md' \
    --set 'files[-1].action=created' \
    --set 'files[].path=/abs/path/to/scripts/foo.sh' \
    --set 'files[-1].action=created'
```

Syntax: `[]` appends, `[-1]` targets the last appended entry.

Limit skill-file writes to
`~/.kiro/skills/<location>/<name>/`.

## Workflow type — render the unified template

For workflow-type designs, do NOT hand-compose SKILL.md.
Render `~/.kiro/skills/home/dojo/templates/skill/workflow.md.j2`
via the `template` skill's `render.sh`.

```bash
TEMPLATE=~/.kiro/skills/home/template/scripts/render.sh
VARS={{ task.workdir }}/vars.json

cat > "$VARS" <<'EOF'
{
  "name": "...",
  "description": "...",
  "title": "...",
  "intro": "...",
  "prefix": "...",
  "shim": "...",
  "skill_name": "...",
  "target": "<...>",
  "dependencies": "- `loom` — ...\n- `tiling` — ...",
  "parameters": "- **...** (required): ...",
  "ingest_args": "--op <create|update>",
  "rules": "1. ...\n2. ...",
  "completion": "| `DONE` | ... |\n| `BLOCKED` | ... |",
  "plan_visualisation": "<loom visualise rail of this skill's plan; \\n-joined>",
  "final_notes": ""
}
EOF

$TEMPLATE \
    --template ~/.kiro/skills/home/dojo/templates/skill/workflow.md.j2 \
    --include-dir ~/.kiro/skills/home/dojo/templates/skill \
    --include-dir ~/.kiro/skills/home/loom/templates \
    --json-vars "$VARS" \
    > ~/.kiro/skills/<location>/<name>/SKILL.md
```

The two `--include-dir` flags register the workflow
template's folder and loom's templates so the partial
{% raw %}`{% include %}`{% endraw %} directives resolve.

### Variable derivation

| Variable        | Source / how to derive                                          |
|-----------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------|
| `name`          | `gather.name`                                                   |
| `description`  | `gather.description` (refined by your design pass if needed)    |
| `title`         | Pretty H1 form, e.g. `gather.name` with `-` → space, title-cased|
| `intro`         | 1–3 sentences explaining what the skill does                    |
| `prefix`        | Uppercase shell prefix from name initials (`SB`, `SR`, …)       |
| `shim`          | Uppercase wrapper-script base name (`BUILDER`, `REVIEWER`, …)   |
| `skill_name`    | Equals `gather.name` for the tiling activity label              |
| `target`        | Placeholder for primary parameter, e.g. `<op>` or `<name>`      |
| `dependencies`  | Markdown bullet list (each item: `` - `<dep>` — note ``)        |
| `parameters`    | Markdown bullet list describing the skill's inputs              |
| `ingest_args`   | Argv tail for the `ingest` call, e.g. `--op <create|update>`    |
| `rules`         | Markdown numbered list of cross-step rules                      |
| `completion`    | Markdown table body rows (no header), one per status            |
| `plan_visualisation` | Build the skill's loom plan (call its plan builder, e.g. `derive_static_plan`, with placeholder CR/arg values) and capture `loom.visualise(plan)` — the very plan you `loom.init`-verify. This populates the `## Plan visualisation` section with the task DAG. Empty string if the skill has no static plan to show. |
| `final_notes`   | Optional trailing prose (empty string if none)                  |

Pick `prefix` and `shim` per workflow-conventions's "Shell
Variable Prefixing" rule. The partial bodies are loom's
source of truth — leave them unmodified; changes belong in
loom.
